insert into Review values (1,'adamau','Perfect',9,'I cannot think of one reason I would not give this 10/10 except out of principle. Otherwise, it is the perfect movie with an incredible story, acting and euphoric finale that nonetheless is not without tragedy.','05-JAN-2022');
insert into Review values (1,'brianmak','All-time prison film classic',10,'Every technical element of the movie is spot-on, from direction to music, editing, and acting; Morgan Freeman delivers his best ever performance whilst Tim Robbins shows us what a great character actor he is. Emotion, thrills, drama, and the triumph of the human spirit are all present in this movie.','09-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (1,'ireneip','Masterpiece',10,'This is a movie about friendship and hope. What makes the movie work so well is that director Durabont takes his time telling a story that takes place over twenty years. Robbins and Freeman are terrific together and really make for one of the most memorable friendships in movie history.','02-JUN-2022');
insert into Review values (5,'shirleysit','A movie for actors',7,'This is the classic stage play. I say this meaning it''s a bunch of characters in a room. The characters don''t even have names. Lee J. Cobb and Jack Warden have the flashiest roles. Henry Fonda is essentially the lead as the central heroic role. He has the nobility. The roles are all filled with first rate character actors. This is an actor''s movie. The only drawback is the cinematic potential. Despite that, the debate interplay is engrossing and the movie is satisfying.','03-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (9,'steviesu','Amazingly original ... but also a bit overwhelming',8,'Out of the Christopher Nolan movies I have seen, Inception didn''t wow me as much as Memento and The Prestige. My main problem was the lack of emotional attachment. The characters are written and acted well, but not much is done to make us empathise with them and their predicaments.','14-JUN-2022');
insert into Review values (14,'terrytam','It''s the middle child of the movie',9,'This is the war. This is the necessary part of the movie to set up the finale. Because it''s the middle child, it doesn''t get the attention or respect. Once one has all three movies in hand, one can begin to view them as a single entity. The series of battles that make up this movie are so incredible. There is not much exposition here, though new characters are made available to us. It is rather to get from point A to point B and make way for the final book.','22-FEB-2022');
insert into Review values (20,'ireneip','Another bloated, overrated space epic',4,'Interstellar has plenty of interesting moments, but the running time is padded and bloated with endless sentimentalism and extraneous characters. Around the middle part of the movie it starts to get weighed down with endless CGI effects; the end part gets muddled and predictable in equal measure.','11-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (20,'adamau','Intellectual, although flawed science fiction',7,'While this movie is, at times, a little confusing in the implications of time and space, it is still quite challenging and interesting. I thought it sort of devolved in a kind of sentimental mess, but the presentation of the problem is worth a viewing.','04-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (20,'rezanlim','Out of this world ',10,'A lot has been said and written about Interstellar. You can obviously take apart any movie that is out there. You''ll either love this one or you won''t. It might be clear to some earlier than to others, where it''s heading, but it doesn''t change the fact that it''s both beautiful ... and terrifying.','08-JAN-2022');
insert into Review values (27,'frankfung','Well made but yecch',7,'I am not a huge fan of thrillers and, in particular, I don''t care for violent or gory movies. The bad news is that this was a gory movie ... a very gory movie. The not so bad news. Although I really didn''t like the movie very much, it was interesting and different. Anthony Hopkins did a nice job playing a psycho murderer--though I also felt this performance was anything but subtle--but it was entertaining.','07-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (35,'fredfan','Scorsese''s Boston gangster opera',8,'Director Martin Scorsese goes to Boston to film this gangster opera. The cast is second to none. There is great acting being done here. Leo is terrific holding up even against the peacock acting of Nicholson. Winstone is powerfully rough. Damon is twisting his sweet persona into something a bit more of a douche. There is a bit too much plot and sometimes, the movie tries to do too many things.','02-APR-2022');
insert into Review values (38,'lesterlo','Great American cinema',9,'This movie is a shocking, revealing portrayal of personal racism. Norton is insanely powerful. Furlong does some solid work as the teen with a chip on his shoulder. This is a movie worthy of recognition.','17-JUN-2022');
insert into Review values (43,'fredfan','A little bit of movie magic',8,'This is a movie about how we start out as small children, trying to make sense out of the world, with nothing to guide us but stories in the dark ... and in the end, we end up that way, nostalgic for a time when we were confident that some day all would be revealed.','15-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (43,'candychan','Friends, this cinema is for you',9,'What''s truly magical about this movie is the special relationship developed between Alfredo and his young ward Toto. He constructs his story with little hints of what leads to the cleverest of conclusions when Salvatore watches the reel that Alfredo leaves for him upon his passing, a touching commentary on life and love that the old man conveys to his former student as a keepsake and reminder of their time together.','25-APR-2022');
insert into Review values (46,'adamau','Admirable',7,'I am not a fan of western genre but this movie is real splendid. First, for the surprising, for me, performance of Henry Fonda. For the music of Ennio Moriccone. And, sure, for the recipe of Sergio Leone, working impeccably. A beautiful revenge movie and inspired portrait of the birth of a town.','01-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (48,'lesterlo','One of Hitch''s best',9,'A taut, intelligent script and two wonderful performances from the leads make Rear Window another of Hitchcock''s masterpieces. The story, about a wheelchair-bound man witnessing a murder is the kind of simple, single-set setup that Hitchcock loved best and he makes full use of the premise by ladling it with humour, suspense and all kinds of tension. Stewart and Kelly make for an irresistible double act and the murder plot is delightfully dark and full of menace.','06-JUN-2022');
insert into Review values (51,'timothytu','Masterpiece',10,'Chaplin made great movies before and after City Lights, but for my money this here is his greatest movie as well as one of the greatest movies ever made. Not only is it one of the funniest movies ever made but I''d also argue that it''s one of the greatest love stories, if not the greatest. It really says a lot when a movie can conqueror two genres at one time but City Lights is simply one of the greatest movies ever made.','20-JAN-2022');
insert into Review values (57,'steviesu','Time to play the (end)game',10,'Endgame is amazing! Epic fights, epic emotions and dialog that is hinting at things to come later in the movie ... which you will see even clearer with repeat viewing(s) ... The Russos did it - Kudos to them, Kevin Feige, Stan Lee (RIP) and everyone else involved in this of course.','08-JUN-2022');
insert into Review values (57,'ireneip','Six stones, three teams, one shot!',8,'I thought the movie was good for what it was, but it took quite a stretch to bring back the characters who went missing following Infinity War. There are a lot of huh? moments in the picture - fat Thor (Chris Hemsworth) is one - why? Thor cutting off Thanos''s head another - too easy, why not any time prior? Stuff like that demeans credibility and took me out of the picture for a moment. In summation, by all means, see the movie, but keep things in perspective.','01-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (60,'kathyko','Tarantino at the top of his game',9,'Django Unchained really does a remarkable job at being a Tarantino movie meaning that everything a fan has come to expect from one of his movies is on full display and perfectly executed. The music score is fabulous, the cinematography highly impressive and the costumes and settings really make you feel as if you''re in the actual period that the movie is set. The movie is very dark, very bloody but oh so funny. It works on all levels including a bloody good revenge tale.','16-FEB-2022');
insert into Review values (63,'fredfan','My child always comes first',10,'The movie brings to light what it is truly like to be dyslexic. Aamir Khan succeeded in creating the awareness about dyslexia thru this movie. Sometimes we really need to step into the shoes of kids and see the world thru their point of view. The irony is that we all were kids, we all went thru the pressure of performing in sports and studies but yet we push our kids, especially in India and China.','11-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (69,'lesterlo','Classic bit of schoolboy action',10,'The story is pure Saturday morning hokum, but it''s all shined up with a great deal of professionalism and you don''t notice. The main strength is the tremendous sense of fun in the movie - not only is it funny but the huge action scenes are all edge of the seat stuff that are hugely enjoyable to watch. Be it the opening set piece, the truck chase, the fight around a burning airplane, the chase for a basket or the gory finish - it''s all great fun to watch.','21-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (69,'ireneip','Not the worst of the trilogy and not the best ',6,'Raiders of the Lost Ark is arguably the movie that in 1981 gave back to the adventure movie its credibility around three points: exoticism, action and effectiveness. This is a movie that hurries things along without any idle times and the one that established Harrison Ford''s reputation, unforgettable and irreplaceable, in Indiana Jones'' role. An awesome movie which the influence on the forthcoming adventure movies will be huge.','01-FEB-2022');
insert into Review values (72,'timothytu','Milestone',9,'The beginning of one of the greatest series of all time. This movie will always remain a classic. It''s scary, influential and insanely entertaining. There''s an interesting mystery surrounding the Alien which we know practically nothing about. Sigourney Weaver is just as powerful as usual and really brings strength to the movie. Last but not least, the musical score. Wow! It''s fantastic. I think the Alien series is known for that aspect as well.','11-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (76,'adamau','One of the greatest anti-war movies',8,'Stanley Kubrick creates one of the classic anti-war movies of all times. Its indictment was biting at the time and finds its glory by the opposition it faced. Kirk Douglas is at his heroic best. The vision is sharp. The story is poignant. The movie finds its target and doesn''t let go.','30-APR-2022');
insert into Review values (83,'fredfan','Not quite up to the hype',9,'American Beauty is an effective and extremely black comedy that attempts to skewer the typical, suburban American family. While that conceit is highly familiar, American Beauty handles it with aplomb. It helps that the excellent Kevin Spacey takes the lead role, and nobody else could have quite grasped the intricacies of his character like he does. Plus he makes his deadbeat lead sympathetic despite his myriad flaws.','02-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (83,'jennyjones','An American tale',7,'I can not compare this movie to anything I have ever seen before. Well written and superbly directed. The acting was so good it made limit pushing activities look somewhat normal. Kevin Spacey is fantastic as the man trapped in a miserable life. Annette Bening is so real as the work obsessed wife with no time for her husband. Thora Birch is pedestrian as the daughter lacking self confidence. Mena Suvari plays the flirtatious tart with zest.','30-APR-2022');
insert into Review values (91,'adamau','The mercurial genius',9,'Amadeus is a wonderful recreation of the court at Schonbrunn Palace in Vienna during the age of reason. What I liked about the movie is that author Peter Shaffer obviously researched with great care the period this rivalry between Salieri and Mozart takes place. Amadeus brought a revival of interest in the old classical masters and that''s always a good thing.','19-FEB-2022');
insert into Review values (91,'vickyyu','That was not Mozart laughing, ... that was God',6,'Almost 10 years after Cuckoo''s Nest, Milos Forman takes us on another travel down the abyss of the human psyche. The actions by and conflict between Antonio Salieri and Mozart are the poignant essence of this movie. In the final act, magically attracted, yet massively repulsed, Salieri schemes Mozart into letting him be an assistant in the mastermind''s creative process. Imperfection becomes more visible than ever. Disaster takes its course.','18-JAN-2022');
insert into Review values (91,'lesterlo','Salieri too! ',7,'Tom Hulce memorably portrays brilliant composer Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart a deeply gifted musician with one big drawback: he is also a vulgar buffoon, with no real appreciation of his talents. F. Murray Abraham plays Antonio Salieri, another contemporary composer who is a sophisticated, cultured gentleman, but unfortunately, who also has only a fraction of Mozart''s talent. It is the philosophical duel between Salieri, Mozart, and God, that make this picture so good.','17-MAR-2022');
insert into Review values (94,'timothytu','Kubrick''s outer space masterpiece',8,'2001: A Space Odyssey is without a doubt the ''ultimate'' space movie. movies like Star Wars or Alien wouldn''t exist without this. The first movie to realistically portray what space travel is actually like. Yes, the movie is incredibly slow, long, and extremely arty, but it''s also a masterpiece and quite possibly Stanley Kubrick''s greatest directorial effort.','19-JUN-2022');
insert into Review values (100,'timothytu','The ultimate crime drama',10,'There is nothing bad I can say about this movie. The acting, the directing, the sound ... all perfect. Many have praised Lang for his use of sound at a time when the practice was just coming into play. And rightfully so. Whereas other movies have sound matching what is on the screen, Lang realized he could use the effect to signify what he was not showing, including the murderer (who has a distinctive whistle). Brilliant.','27-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (101,'adamau','The tyranny of the dollar',5,'Frances McDormand loses her job and lives out of a van, working seasonal jobs at Amazon. She works less, vacations more, but has to poop in a bucket and give herself bad haircuts. She hangs out sometimes with folks like herself who celebrate their poverty as a way to getting back to nature. The nomads are the throwaways of society finding some solace in community. The movie was boring and theme-driven. I find it amazing that it was even nominated for best picture, let alone won the award.','12-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (107,'rezanlim','Degradation and despair',8,'For me, 12 Years a Slave is not quite as good as the hype and isn''t one of my favourite Best Picture winners. It could have been truly extraordinary, but it wasn''t quite despite having individual elements that were that adjective. The acting is superb, with Chiwetel Ejiofor''s powerfully restrained and sincere performance wholly deserving of its acclaim. Overall, extraordinary it isn''t but an emotionally impactful movie it certainly is.','24-MAR-2022');
insert into Review values (111,'larrylai','The bomb (pun intended)',9,'A movie that actually feels more like a documentary, this begins with a big bang (pun again intended). And whether you like what you see or not, it is absolutely well shot and executed (pun this time not intended). The actors are so into their characters that you don''t realize they''re only playing. A movie that has messages, but is more an examination of human behavior under certain circumstances, than anything else.','22-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (115,'walterwu','A depressing experience',4,'I''ve loved the majority of Eastwood''s movies as director, but this movie left me cold. On the face of it, there''s nothing much to dislike: it''s expertly crafted with Eastwood''s eye for technical detail and cast members delivering Oscar-winning performances. Nonetheless, something didn''t gel with me. Despite the professionalism of its cast and crew, Million Dollar Baby forgets to be entertaining, and I disliked it for that reason.','12-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (115,'adamau','Clint Eastwood turns in another great movie ',8,'This is a great standard underdog sports story for 3/4 of the movie. It works great. Clint and Morgan are old hands at this. They cancel each other a bit with their grumbling voices and their gruff demeanor. Hilary Swank is perfect for the role. She''s no princess. She can definitely play the hungry white trash role. Then the last 30 minutes turn dark. It''s a change in tone. It has difficult things to say. If it could be edited down, it could be even better.','29-APR-2022');
insert into Review values (115,'fredfan','A story of redemption',9,'When you make a movie with characters, true characters, you have won half the battle. The characters in this movie are on a crash course with emptiness, until they find each other. The movie is, of course, ultimately about love: love for self, love for others, and love for why we are put on this earth. I was really moved by this movie. It is a masterpiece of redemption and will. It is about victory through pain.','31-MAR-2022');
insert into Review values (119,'jennyjones','Beautiful. Maybe',7,'For a movie that was made almost 25 years ago it holds up extremely well in picture and sound. Dicaprio and Winslet are, of course, marvelous in their roles but for me Billy Zane is the best here, the way he plays the demanding rich American taking his British teenage fiancée back home, only to be interrupted by the carefree Jack who presents a completely different outlook on life. This will remain a classic for many decades to come, well deserving of its various awards.','25-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (125,'vickyyu','Worth seeing',8,'The best thing going for Guardians is that with the huge glut of super-hero movies during the last decade or so, this one manages to stand apart--something that cannot be said of most of the movies. There is just a certain sameness that make me less than thrilled with all the comic book hero movies. But a few, like this movie, manage to seem different enough to merit your rushing to see them.','18-MAR-2022');
insert into Review values (125,'adamau','A galaxy full of fun',8,'This is a rip-roaring fun space opera. Chris Pratt is at the top of his game. This is a bright, wild, crazy ride. There is a lot of Marvel lore to go through for the uninitiated. That''s probably my main concern about this movie. The 70s soundtrack is a terrific touch and the humor is infectious.','28-FEB-2022');
insert into Review values (125,'jennyjones','Escape',5,'With Guardians of the Galaxy, Marvel has gone to the C list of their comic book heroes. The movie takes it cue from some post modern Star Wars mixed with Indiana Jones in space. However a bunch of misfits who argue and mistrust each other before putting away their differences and uniting to fight a common foe was played out in The Avengers movie.','06-JUN-2022');
insert into Review values (125,'xavierxie','This is really Groot!',10,'There is a lot going for the movie and if you love science fiction, this might not have sounded like a shoo-in. I myself never thought I''d like this movie so much. But how could I think Marvel could go wrong? I don''t know, but of course they didn''t. They choose their directors wisely and their cast wisely too. Chris Pratt is someone you might have seen in many comedies before, all with small budgets or him in a supporting role ... things are about to be changed! People will know his name.','27-APR-2022');
insert into Review values (125,'terrytam','A really fun space opera',8,'When I saw that this was a Marvel movie I initially thought it might be yet another superhero movie; it isn''t. Instead we get a space opera which is full of action, humour and some fine lead characters. The plot might not provide too many surprises but it does give exciting scene after exciting scene. The characters are great; I particularly liked Groot. Overall I''d say this is a really fun sci-fi romp that can be enjoyed by anybody who enjoys the genre but doesn''t take it too seriously.','17-JAN-2022');
insert into Review values (125,'timothytu','Wow. Just wow…',7,'What worked for me in Guardians of the Galaxy was a couple of things. First, the storyline was really entertaining from start to end. It was a story that you could submerge yourself into because there were so many aspects to it that there was just something for just about everyone. Second, I was blown away by the special effects, especially because it was so realistic and so vivid; lots of color and vibrant things on the screen throughout the movie.','28-JUN-2022');
insert into Review values (131,'adamau','Great actors in memorable roles',8,'Adapted from Seven Samurai, what makes this movie great is the memorable characters. Eli Wallach is one of the greatest spaghetti western actors of all time, and he makes this villain iconic. And the seven heroes are all individuals. They all fit their roles well. Each are given enough time to develop their roles. There are good action scenes. There are some funny lines. It deserves its iconic status.','01-JUN-2022');
insert into Review values (133,'timothytu','Not perfect, but very good on the whole',7,'I do not think this is John Wayne''s best movie or role, but I did like this movie, though I do not think it is perfect. While the movie starts and ends very well, the movie slackens in pace in the middle. However, the movie does look great. Handsomely shot with great scenery, True Grit is pleasing to the eye.','29-APR-2022');
insert into Review values (134,'candychan','Makes some improvements over the 1969 film',9,'True Grit isn''t really a remake as such, but as a more faithful take on the novel. And even if it were a remake, it is one of the better ones. While I did like the 1969 movie very much, this version does make some improvements, such as the pace and Mattie. But it also has some hindrances; the ending is abrupt, and some of the characters perhaps are not quite as intriguing as they are in the 1969 movie. All in all, a great movie.','05-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (138,'walterwu','A good way to spoil an interesting subject',4,'This movie is something of a biopic of Abraham Lincoln, although it only focuses on the most important parts of his life, inevitably those surrounding the American Civil War and the 13th Amendment. My question is, why does this movie need to be two and a half hours long? Politics can be a dry topic to make a movie out of in any case, and all Spielberg succeeds in doing is boring his viewer with one boring, talky, drawn-out scene after another.','12-APR-2022');
insert into Review values (141,'adamau','Coen brothers'' black comedy masterpiece',9,'This is a great movie. It has its funny moments. It has great visual touches, the quirky characters, and the off-kilter style that is the hallmark of the Coen brothers. Macy is incredible as the sniffling little weasel. It walks the absurd line between dark and comedy. It has plenty of both. It is simply wonderful.','06-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (147,'adamau','Clever, intense Sci-Fi spectacle',9,'Wow - this was unexpected. The trailers had me believe that after ''Battle L.A.'' and ''Oblivion'' this would be yet another bleak, action-packed, special effects driven Sci-Fi blockbuster about an alien invasion - what the trailers failed to convey almost entirely is that over long stretches, this is also seasoned with nearly as much humor as ''Groundhog Day''.','06-MAR-2022');
insert into Review values (147,'frankfung','What a Fantastic Movie! ',10,'This science fiction story is deeply satisfying. The movie treats the viewers as intelligent people. It is not in the same league of a plethora of science fiction movies that hit the cinemas every year.','06-APR-2022');
insert into Review values (147,'terrytam','Amazing',9,'When you have a movie that has a massive budget with spectacular action and effects and doesn''t mess up the plot, story, or characters, like the Edge of Tomorrow does, then that''s when you''ve got yourself a good movie. Plus the plot is a good one that the movie gave us time to understand. Every actor/actress did a great job at their role in the movie. The characters were well developed. The action and effects are phenomenal. Everything about this movie is amazing!','10-FEB-2022');
insert into Review values (148,'frankfung','"Talk to me, Goose."',7,'Hot shot fighter pilot Maverick (Tom Cruise) clashes with other pilots at Top Gun School while trying to prove himself and live down his father''s bad reputation. He also makes time to get sexy with instructor Kelly McGillis, who may or may not have lost that lovin'' feelin''. What an awesome movie.','06-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (148,'terrytam','Legendary ',8,'It is bizarre to define it or to give an opinion about it. It is legendary, the perfect mix of heroism, love, soundtrack and... Tom Cruise, rivalry and fly. Maybe, its lovely simplicity is the key of huge success. And the discovery of basic, small things defining us.','06-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (148,'adamau','Entertaining no brainer',6,'Top Gun is a high quality, visually stunning film that does all it can to take your breath away. It is the excellently choreographed dog fights that remain in the mind longer than anything as they are high octane, dazzling bursts of excitement which bring the film to life. However, fighter jet sequences do not make a film and it is the plot where Top Gun has some occasional problems.','04-MAY-2022');
insert into Review values (29,'adamau','So Close To Perfection',9,'Seven Samurai is pretty great, but I think Harakiri is even better. This tale of a ronin seeking revenge and exposing the flawed samurai code is so close to perfection. The story is engrossing and despite the slow pacing it''s never boring. What the production lacks in scale it makes up for with emotional intensity. The sparse, ominous score is perfect for this film. The direction and cinematography are masterful and the camera''s slow pans and zooms really butter my croissant.','28-FEB-2022');
insert into Review values (89,'lesterlo','Matches the brilliance of the first film',10,'Series note: It is strongly advised that you watch this film only after seeing Alien (1979). This is a direct continuation of that story. Aliens is yet another example of a sequel that is just as good as an original film in a series. Just make sure you watch both in order, and try to watch the director''s cuts.','25-MAR-2022');
insert into Review values (89,'yvonneyu','One of the best films ever made',10,'So often when you think of sequels you imagine cynical attempts to cash in on successful movies, efforts to bring in the coins with any old rubbish. Not often is a follow up as good as the original (and better in some ways,) but Aliens is, I would class it as one of the best movies of all time, a cinematic Masterpiece which seems to improve with age. It''s a space horror, which is dramatic, action packed and funny at times.','17-JUN-2022');
insert into Review values (89,'rezanlim','This is how it''s done, you morons',9,'Welcome to 1986, where they had diverse AND well-written characters in what has to be one of the best Sci-Fi Action films of all time. Even in 1979, Ellen Ripley was what those wannabes today want to recreate: a strong, yet believable female character with a real challenge and a highly competent movie around her. Go watch this movie!','02-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (44,'ireneip','A magnificent piece of work',8,'I''m not a big fan of animation, but there are some films that are so great that a person''s personal preferences are irrelevant, and this is one of those films. Through it''s well observed and very real characters, Grave of the Fireflies portrays a story of loss, heartbreak and the effect of war on civilians in a manner that is more effective and more firmly based in reality than many live action films about the same subject are.','07-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (44,'lesterlo','A film that shows the true cost of war',10,'I was nearly moved to tears by this film''s brave treatment of such critical subject matter. "Grave of the Fireflies" is a bold statement on the condition of the human soul during conflict. It''s brave, it''s not overly sentimental, but it is relentless in its dramatization of a dangerous reality. A beautiful film; not to be missed by anyone.','19-JAN-2022');
insert into Review values (61,'walterwu','A wonderful conclusion to a wonderful trilogy',9,'The Dark Knight Rises was a perfect sequel to a masterpiece. Christopher Nolan took a different direction and focused more on Bruce Wayne/Batman. This movie is filled with lots of emotions. It has such great characters and of course the dialogs is so good. The performances are incredible. It was my most anticipated movie of the century.','29-MAR-2022');
insert into Review values (61,'peterpoon','Boys, Playing It Cool',3,'One for Joseph Gordon-Levitt''s fresh and believable take on the rookie cop with street smarts, ideals and courage. One for Anne Hathaway''s purr-fect performance as the Catwoman. One for an aging Michael Caine, in memory of the man who was a king. Beyond that, it''s all a murky sea of meaningless explosions, sodden speeches, missed opportunities, and plot holes you could drive the Batmobile through.','04-JUL-2022');
insert into Review values (61,'henryho','A fun ride to be on',9,'I love that this is all one big action sequence. It really keeps you on your toes with a Lord of The Rings type war story for the climax. A good movie for someone who looks for a thrill.','29-APR-2022');
insert into Review values (74,'monicama','Sharp and outrageously entertaining',10,'Wow. What a terrific, pitch black satire. This film is so wild and mean and funny - and Peter Sellers gives THE performance of his career. Unlike in any of Kubrick''s later works, there''s a sense of playfulness here that gives the whole movie a crazy kind of energy. Sharp, outrageously entertaining comedy/satire by one of the most revered directors of the past century.','21-MAR-2022');
insert into Review values (74,'walterwu','Russians In The War Room',10,'Art has a way to warn, express or simply entertain in a way that its relevance will always be renewed. The film doesn''t have a moment of emptiness nor a single cheap shot. Everything works with the irrational logic of tradition and set standards. How can something so serious and ultimately terrifying be so funny? I think that''s the definition of film art.','31-MAR-2022');
insert into Review values (74,'fredfan','...I don''t get it',6,'Yeah. It was funny. It was entertaining. It''s not a bad movie by any means. I think Kubrick did a great job with the visuals and the settings. Beyond that, it''s not very dramatic or suspenseful. There''s not much depth or intellect. The premise was interesting. Perhaps the general and his descent into madness could''ve used more fleshing out. I don''t know. It feels like it''s missing something.','02-FEB-2022');
